---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility | Healthy Paws Animal Hospital"
  description="Accessibility commitment statement for Healthy Paws Animal Hospital. We are committed to ensuring our website is accessible to all visitors."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-hpah-green-light py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl mb-4">Accessibility</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-hpah-text-light max-w-2xl">
        We are committed to making our website accessible and usable for everyone,
        regardless of ability or technology.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accessibility Content -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose">

        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          {business.name} is committed to ensuring that our website is accessible to all
          visitors, including those with disabilities. We believe that every pet owner
          deserves equal access to information about their pet's care, our services, and
          our practice — regardless of how they access our website.
        </p>
        <p>
          Accessibility isn't just a technical requirement for us — it reflects the same
          values we bring to veterinary medicine: inclusivity, thoughtfulness, and a
          genuine desire to help everyone who comes through our doors (physical or digital).
        </p>

        <h2>Conformance Goal</h2>
        <p>
          We strive to conform to the <strong>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1,
          Level AA</strong> standards. These guidelines, developed by the World Wide Web
          Consortium (W3C), provide a framework for making web content more accessible to
          people with a wide range of disabilities, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Visual impairments (blindness, low vision, color blindness)</li>
          <li>Hearing impairments</li>
          <li>Motor impairments</li>
          <li>Cognitive and learning disabilities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Measures We Take</h2>
        <p>
          To support our accessibility goals, we have implemented the following measures:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> We use proper heading structures, landmarks, and semantic elements to ensure our content is navigable by screen readers and assistive technologies.</li>
          <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> All interactive elements on our website are accessible via keyboard navigation.</li>
          <li><strong>Alternative text:</strong> Images include descriptive alt text to convey their content and purpose to screen reader users.</li>
          <li><strong>Color contrast:</strong> We maintain sufficient color contrast ratios between text and backgrounds to ensure readability.</li>
          <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Our website adapts to different screen sizes and zoom levels without loss of content or functionality.</li>
          <li><strong>Clear link text:</strong> Links are descriptive and clearly indicate their destination or purpose.</li>
          <li><strong>Skip navigation:</strong> A "skip to content" link is provided for keyboard users to bypass repetitive navigation.</li>
          <li><strong>Form accessibility:</strong> Form fields include proper labels and error messages that are announced by screen readers.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Ongoing Efforts</h2>
        <p>
          Accessibility is an ongoing effort, not a one-time project. We regularly review
          and test our website to identify and address accessibility barriers. We are
          committed to continual improvement as technology and standards evolve.
        </p>

        <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
        <p>
          While we strive for full accessibility, some third-party content embedded on our
          website (such as the Google Maps iframe on our contact page) may have accessibility
          limitations outside our direct control. We work to provide alternative access to
          the same information wherever possible — for example, our full address is provided
          as text alongside the map.
        </p>

        <h2>Feedback &amp; Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Your feedback is important to us. If you encounter any accessibility barriers on our
          website, or if you have suggestions for how we can improve accessibility, please
          let us know. We take all feedback seriously and will do our best to address concerns
          promptly.
        </p>
        <p>You can reach us through the following channels:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href={`tel:${business.phoneRaw}`}>{business.phone}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mail:</strong> {business.name}, {business.address.full}</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          When reporting an accessibility issue, it is helpful to include the following information:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The web page URL where the issue occurred</li>
          <li>A description of the issue you encountered</li>
          <li>The assistive technology you were using (if applicable)</li>
          <li>Your preferred method of contact for our response</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We will make every reasonable effort to respond to accessibility feedback within
          5 business days and to resolve identified issues as quickly as possible.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA />
</BaseLayout>
